50|$|The {{room was}} made for the Queen by the same team of artists and {{craftsmen}} who also made the game room; the design was made the architect Pierre Rousseau; the wood panelling was sculpted by Laplace, and painted by Michel-Hubert Bourgeois and Louis-François Touzé. Eight figures of the Muses were made in plaster by Roland; the ornate mantle of the fireplace was made by Jacques-François Dropsy, and decorated with glided bronze works by Claude-Jean <b>Pitoin.</b> The mahogany parquet floor, decorated with the emblems of the Queen, was made by Bernard Molitor, and finished in 1787. The painted ceiling, by Jean-Simon Berthélemy, shows Aurora {{with a group of}} angels.|$|E

